Dynamic table display template for SemanticSchemas categories.

Composes display-header, the property rows, render-reverse, and
subobjects into a full-width wikitable layout.

Two property-row rendering paths:

* '''Fast path (baked)''' — when the caller passes `props` (comma-separated
  parameter-name list) plus per-property `val_<param>` and `label_<param>`,
  iterate the baked list inline with no SMW queries. Auto-generated
  dispatcher templates use this.
* '''Dynamic fallback''' — when `props` is absent, delegate to
  `Category/display-rows` which discovers properties via ancestor walk.
  Used by `Category/subobject-instance` and hand-written custom-display
  wikitext.

Render-reverse (backlinks) and subobjects remain on the dynamic path;
they are gated behind separate property lists on the category.

Parameters:
* category - The category name (without namespace prefix). Required.
* label    - Optional baked category display label (forwarded to
             `Category/display-header`).
* props    - Optional comma-separated parameter-name list that triggers
             the baked row path.
* val_<p>  - Per-property value, one per entry in `props`.
* label_<p> - Per-property display label, one per entry in `props`.
* page     - Target page to read property values from on the dynamic
             path. Defaults to {{FULLPAGENAME}};
             `Category/subobject-instance` passes a subobject fragment
             here so the same template renders individual instances.
* subobjects - Set to "no" to suppress the subobject and backlink
             sections (used by `Category/subobject-instance` to prevent
             recursion).
</noinclude>
